content.text:
The issue was that `ParameterListWrappingRule` would report an "Unnecessary newline" violation on the opening parenthesis of a function type's parameter list when that function type was wrapped inside a nullable type (e.g., `((...) -> Unit)?`). Additionally, it was failing to wrap the inner parameter list even when it exceeded the maximum line length due to a blanket exclusion for function types wrapped in nullable types.

I fixed this by:
1.  Modifying `needToWrapParameterList` in `ParameterListWrappingRule.kt` to allow wrapping of parameter lists inside nullable types if they exceed the maximum line length. The check now correctly calculates the line length based on the expected indentation of the wrapped line to avoid stale column issues during AST modification.
2.  Modifying `wrapParameterInList` to suppress the "Unnecessary newline before '('" error if the newline was introduced by the wrapping of the parent nullable type.

I verified the fix by running the existing `Issue 1255` test case (which confirms correct behavior when the inner list fits on the line) and creating a reproduction test case (which confirms correct behavior when the inner list exceeds the line length and needs wrapping). Both tests pass.

```kotlin
// ktlint-ruleset-standard/src/main/kotlin/com/pinterest/ktlint/ruleset/standard/rules/ParameterListWrappingRule.kt

// In needToWrapParameterList:
// Removed the blanket exclusion: isFunctionTypeWrappedInNullableType() -> false
// Added logic to check if it fits on the new line:
            isFunctionTypeWrappedInNullableType() -> {
                val parentIndent = treeParent?.treeParent?.indent(false) ?: ""
                val indentLevel = indentConfig.indentLevelFrom(parentIndent)
                val newIndentLength = (indentLevel + 1) * indentConfig.indent.length
                (newIndentLength + textLength) > maxLineLength
            }

// In wrapParameterInList:
// Added suppression for unnecessary newline error:
            LPAR -> {
                val prevLeaf = child.prevLeaf()
                if (prevLeaf is PsiWhiteSpace && prevLeaf.textContains('\n')) {
                    if (child.treeParent.isFunctionTypeWrappedInNullableType()) {
                        return
                    }
                    emit(child.startOffset, errorMessage(child), true)
                    // ...
                }
            }
```

